yPlaceholder` if a placeholder exists. Once I click the input to open the dropdown, I can select the option by its visible text using `getByRole('option')`. I'm selecting the first combobox in the step builder, clicking it, filling in 'Page Viewed', then clicking the matching option from the dropdown. For the seed data in beforeAll, I can use the `request` fixture that Playwright provides to make a POST call to the seed endpoint.\n\nNow I'm thinking through the Playwright configuration - I should set `reuseExistingServer` to true since we're likely running against an existing dev server, though I need to be careful about how this interacts with CI environments where the server might not be pre-running.\n\nFor the actual config, I'll set the `baseURL` to localhost:3000, configure the web server to run `pnpm dev` (which already has migration hooks built in), and keep it to just chromium for faster test runs. I also need to migrate any existing tests that hardcode the base URL to use relative paths instead. I see that absolute URLs will still work even with `baseURL` set, so the existing tests won't break. Now I'm thinking through the identity test implementation—I need to create unique IDs for each run, set up two device IDs linked to the same user, and verify they cluster together. The main challenge is working with the custom event form, which requires clicking to expand it, then filling in the event name, device ID, and user ID before sending, and I'll need to repeat this flow for the second device.\n\nSince the form doesn't reset its fields after submission, I can keep it open and just update the Device ID field for the second event rather than collapsing and re-expanding. After the first send with deviceA, I'll clear that field, enter deviceB, and submit again while keeping the event name and user ID the same.\n\nNow I'm thinking through the identity spec constraints—linking multiple devices to the same user is allowed, so I can send one event with deviceA + uniqueUser, then another with deviceB + uniqueUser without hitting a 409 conflict, as long as deviceA wasn't previously linked to a different user.\n\nFor the userProfile test, I need to navigate to the profile page and check that the identity cluster displays correctly and the event count reaches at least 5. The page is a Server Component that fetches the user profile and displays the event timeline with a count in the heading. I'm looking at how the \"Identify User\" button constructs its payload to understand what event gets logged. I need to look at the `useEventSender` hook to understand how `lastDeviceId` gets updated and whether it's being reset unexpectedly when different buttons are clicked.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":967,"cache_read_input_tokens":61141,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":967},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eb1717ec-5d87-4414-9ed1-88e4656c8afb","uuid":"9bfde83a-8cd0-4cf4-a3bc-81534e53224c"}
